          "scid": "thig2.8:1.0.3",
          "en": "8. Abhayā's Mother"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.8:1.0.4",
          "en": "“‘Upward from sole of foot, O mother dear, Downward from crown of hair this body see. Is’t not impure, the evil-smelling thing?’ This have I pondered, meditating still, Till every throb of lust is rooted out. Expunged is all the fever of desire. Cool am I now and calm—Nibbana’s peace.”"
        }
